input_full.title: Inspection skill: agent-driven visual QA from fresh builds
input_full.body:
A new `/inspect` skill that uses the existing agenting framework (Claude Code skill, MCP tool deployment, archival integration, workflow gated by testing) to perform intelligent visual QA.

**Proposed workflow:**

1. **Build & capture:** Build a showcase repo (SBSTest, GCR, or PNT) and capture screenshots on every page
2. **Context loading:** Deploy an agent fed with:
   - The full test catalogue (non-dev items only)
   - All SBS-related GitHub issues (open + closed for historical context)
   - This gives the agent complete understanding of what we track and bugs we've fixed
3. **Visual inspection:** Agent examines screenshots from the fresh build and reports issues using its intelligence — not just pattern-matching against validators, but genuine visual assessment
4. **Multi-pass automation:** If context limits prevent reviewing all images in one pass, automatically chunk and run multiple agent passes until all pages are covered. Leverage agent intelligence to determine chunking strategy.

**Key design principles:**
- Builds on existing infrastructure (MCP tools, archive, skill framework)
- Complements deterministic validators (T1-T8) with intelligent visual review
- Agent has full issue history context, so it can catch regressions and known-pattern recurrences
- Output should be actionable: new issues logged, or confirmation that pages look clean

---
